  <section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="rv-q"><h3>Who is the best window replacement company in North Texas?</h3><p>Maverick Windows is the highest-scored in our 2026 ranking (4.8★, ~1,307 reviews). Brennan Enterprises and Statewide Energy Solutions also score strongly. The right choice depends on your city, window material and budget — get two or three written bids.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>Do window replacement companies need a license in Texas?</h3><p>Window replacement is not a state-licensed trade in Texas, so there is no master license number to look up the way there is for plumbers or electricians. Instead, verify real credentials: ENERGY STAR partnership, AAMA/NFRC product certification, manufacturer-authorized dealer status, and BBB accreditation. Our list shows the credentials we could confirm for each company, or a dash where we could not verify one.</p></div><div class="rv-q"><h3>How were these companies ranked?</h3><p>Each company is scored on verified Google/Yelp/BBB ratings and review volume, years in business, manufacturer certifications, and service depth. Figures come from public profiles as of June 2026, are re-checked monthly, and no company paid for placement.</p></div></section>

